thread.title: Building approvals rise in July

title: Building approvals rise in July
text:
View Photo 

Approvals for the construction of new homes rose 4.2 per cent in July, which was better than market expectations of a three per cent rise. 
Over the 12 months to July, building approvals were up 13.4 per cent, the Australian Bureau of Statistics said on Tuesday. 
Approvals for private sector houses fell 3.0 per cent in the month, and the 'other dwellings' category, which includes apartment blocks and townhouses, was up 6.1 per cent. @YahooNZBusiness on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Building approvals rise in July AAP
